Mastodome 0.3.6 (2020-01-21)
* Fixed a security vulnerability in the validators Python dependency

Mastodome 0.3.5 (2019-07-05)
* Updated links to helpful resources in README.md

Mastodome 0.3.4 (2019-06-24)
* Blocks sign-ins from server URLs containing "gab."

Mastodome 0.3.3 (2019-05-19)
* Updates project name and status in README.md

Mastodome 0.3.2 (2019-05-06)
* Updates project status in README.md
* Updates links in README.md

Mastodome 0.3.1 (2019-04-01)
* Removes legacy license notices that no longer apply
* Removes CoC file that no longer applies (as project not active)
* Updates links in README.md
* Fixes installation instructions in README.md

Mastodome 0.3 (2019-01-25)
* Removes assets licensed under AGPL by Mastodon project
* Re-licenses Mastodome under MIT terms
* Updates README
* Sets fixed versions for pip dependencies
* Sets executable permissions for mastodome.py by default

Mastodome 0.2 (2018-11-21)
* Runs on Python 3 and Qt 5
* Fixes broken keyboard shortcuts
* Enables users to resize the main window
* Remembers previous logins and supports switching between them
* Highlights user interaction at the top of each toot in the stream
* Displays alt text for images in toots
* Displays timestamp for when toots are posted (and boosted)
* Shows content warnings as subjects in the stream
* Shows full notification text
* Posts toots with content warnings and differing privacy levels. Also auto-selects default privacy level
* Removes the status label

Mastodome 0.1 (2018-01-31)
* Supports Login and logout for one Mastodon account at a time (tokens are stored in the local keystore)
* Posts plain text toots up to 280 characters in size (you can edit this limit in config/config.py)
* Fetches read-only notifications that point at URLs
* Fetches read-only toots from your home, local and public streams
* Displays user avatars and display names next to toots and notifications
* Displays the plain-text contents of toots and whether they're a boost or reply
* Caches avatar images to save bandwidth and speed up load times (stored in config/.cache. This is cleared when you use File > Logout...)
* Refreshes both visible panels (use Edit > Refresh or the F5 key)
* Supports the use of translation files (See config/config.py and config/lang/en.json)
